			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>A metal pole, about 1 foot long, ends in a spinning, multicolored disk. A switch on the end of the pole controls the spinning rate of the disk, and this switch is warm to the touch.</i></p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Implement</b><b>:</b> Wand</p>\n<p class=\"basics\"><b>Enhancement Bonus:</b> Attack Rolls and Damage Rolls</p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Critical:</b> +4d8 psychic critical damage</p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Property:</b></p> <p>Malfunction: When you roll a 1 on an attack roll with this wand, you are dominated by the target of the attack against whom you rolled the 1 until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Power âœ¦ At-Will (Standard Action)</b></p><p><i>Attack:</i> Ranged 5 (one creature); wand's level + 3 vs. Will</p><p><i>Hit:</i> 2d6 psychic damage, and the target is dazed (save ends). Until this effect ends, you can use a free action at the start of each of your turns to slide the target up to 5 squares.</p><p>Level 15 or 20: 3d6 psychic damage.</p><p>Level 25 or 30: 4d6 psychic damage.</p>",
